Jenna Etheridge, News24Taxi rank. (Duncan Alfreds, News24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - A Bloemfontein hawker is in a critical condition after he was shot five times on Monday morning, Free State police said.The hawker, a Lesotho national who operated at the Majaka-thata taxi rank in the city centre, was targeted around 06:00, said Constable Wendy Nkabi.The unidentified shooter was still on the run after fleeing the scene.Nkabi appealed for information on the suspect's whereabouts or the circumstances of the shooting.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.